						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 5 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold made by <hi rend="bold">Śaḍaiyaṉ Kalachchi</hi> on behalf of <hi rend="bold">Saḍaiyaṉ Na[m*]bi of Pāmbayūr</hi>, probably her deceased husband, for feeding with the interest there on 15 <hi rend="italic">Māhēśvaras</hi> daily during the seven-day festival of Māśi-Makham, in the temple of Tirumēṟṟaḷi-Perumānaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu. This is very probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> (No. 57, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ind.</hi> Texts).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
